  "text": "All confocal microscopy was performed with a TCS SP5 DM6000B confocal microscope using an HCX PL APO CS 100.0x1.40 OIL lens and LAS AF software (Leica Microsystems). GFP (or YFP) and propidium iodine signals were observed simultaneously on separate channels. The GFP (or YFP) signal was excited using the argon 488-nm laser line and observed using a bandwidth for PMT2 of 490 to 550 nm. The propidium iodide signal was excited using the DPSS 561-nm laser line and observed using a bandwidth for PMT3 of 598 to 656 nm. Confocal images were obtained from transgenic plants and controls grown at 308C to reduce silencing (J. Li, personal communication). Prior to imaging, roots were stained for 30 s in 10 mg/mL propidium iodide in water. For the plasmolysis experiments, the roots were treated with 0.8 M mannitol for 2 h with shaking prior to staining with 10 mg/mL propidium iodide in 0.8 M mannitol. GUS staining was performed, as described [CITATION_1] , on 4-d-old seedlings grown at 308C. Phenotypic quantification was performed using a light microscope and Vernier calipers.",
